To normalize the provided profile data according to the specified guidelines, I'll follow the normalization instructions for each relevant field. Let's process the input profile and return the normalized version.

### Input Profile
```json
{
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "title": "VP of Eng.",
  "location": "SF Bay Area",
  "key_skills": [
    "Java",
    "Agile Methodologies",
    "Team Leadership"
  ],
  "experience": [
    {
      "company": "tech solutions inc",
      "title": "VP, Engineering",
      "duration": {
        "start_date": "March 2018",
        "end_date": "Present",
        "date_range": "5 years 7 months"
      },
      "location": "San Francisco"
    },
    {
      "company": "Innovatech",
      "title": "Sr. Software Engineer",
      "duration": {
        "start_date": "June 2015",
        "end_date": "February 2018",
        "date_range": "2 years 9 months"
      },
      "location": "San Francisco, CA"
    }
  ]
}
```

### Normalized Profile
```json
{
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "title": "Vice President of Engineering",
  "location": "San Francisco, California, United States",
  "key_skills": [
    "Java",
    "Agile Methodologies",
    "Team Leadership"
  ],
  "experience": [
    {
      "company": "Tech Solutions Inc.",
      "title": "Vice President of Engineering",
      "duration": {
        "start_date": "2018-03",
        "end_date": "Present",
        "date_range": "5 years 7 months"
      },
      "location": "San Francisco, California, United States"
    },
    {
      "company": "Innovatech",
      "title": "Senior Software Engineer",
      "duration": {
        "start_date": "2015-06",
        "end_date": "2018-02",
        "date_range": "2 years 9 months"
      },
      "location": "San Francisco, California, United States"
    }
  ],
  "normalization_notes": "Standardized SF Bay Area to full city name; Expanded VP and Sr. abbreviations; Standardized company name capitalization."
}
```

### Explanation of Changes
1. **Title**: Expanded "VP" to "Vice President" and "Eng." to "Engineering".
2. **Location**: Converted "SF Bay Area" to "San Francisco, California, United States".
3. **Company Names**: Capitalized "tech solutions inc" to "Tech Solutions Inc.".
4. **Experience Titles**: Expanded "VP" to "Vice President" and "Sr." to "Senior".
5. **Experience Locations**: Standardized "San Francisco" and "San Francisco, CA" to "San Francisco, California, United States".
6. **Dates**: Converted date formats to ISO format (YYYY-MM).

These changes ensure consistency and clarity across the profile data, making it suitable for downstream analysis and clustering.
